articles.author: Alexandra Ulmer, Gram Slattery
articles.description: Some Republican officials, donors and advisers said Donald Trump, the Republican presidential candidate, had botched his debate with Democratic Vice President Kamala Harris although Trump himself praised his performance.
articles.title: While Trump touts his debate performance, allies, donors and advisers lament it

articles.author: Ted Hesson, Andy Sullivan, Gabriella Borter
articles.description: Haitian Americans said they fear for their safety after Donald Trump repeated a false and derogatory claim during this week's presidential debate about immigrants in Ohio.
articles.title: Haitian Americans fear for their safety after Trump repeats false claims about immigrants

articles.author: Daphne Psaledakis, Olena Harmash
articles.description: U.S. Secretary of State Antony Blinken and British foreign minister David Lammy met top officials in Kyiv on Wednesday, a visit that President Volodymyr Zelenskiy said he hoped would yield "strong" new decisions to support Ukraine.
articles.title: Blinken, UK's Lammy visit Ukraine in show of support at key juncture in war

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: The Palestinian Hamas group said on Wednesday that its negotiators reiterated its readiness to implement an "immediate" ceasefire with Israel in Gaza based on a previous U.S. proposal without new conditions from any party.
articles.title: Hamas says ready to implement ceasefire without new conditions

articles.author: Michelle Nichols
articles.description: A lack of accountability for the killing of United Nations staff and humanitarian aid workers in the Gaza Strip is "totally unacceptable," U.N. Secretary-General Antonio Guterres told Reuters in a wide-ranging interview on Wednesday.
articles.title: UN chief says lack of accountability on UN staff killings in Gaza 'unacceptable'

articles.author: Ali Sawafta
articles.description: An Israeli airstrike killed at least five people in the West Bank city of Tubas on Wednesday, Palestinian emergency services said, as Israeli security forces continued an extended operation that the military said targeted Iranian-backed militant groups.
articles.title: At least 5 reported killed in West Bank airstrike as Israeli raids continue

articles.author: Catarina Demony
articles.description: All three candidates running to become the next secretary-general of the Commonwealth, a 56-nation club headed by Britain's King Charles, said on Wednesday they supported reparations for transatlantic slavery and colonialism.
articles.title: Slavery reparations backed by all candidates vying for Commonwealth boss

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Argentine protesters clashed with police outside the country's Congress on Wednesday, after lower house lawmakers voted to block a planned hike to pensions that had been opposed by right-wing libertarian President Javier Milei.
articles.title: Clashes outside Argentina Congress after pension hike blocked

articles.author: Kiyoshi Takenaka
articles.description: Former defence minister Shigeru Ishiba is corporate Japan's top choice to replace Prime Minister Fumio Kishida, edging out Sanae Takaichi, who strives to become the nation's first female premier, a Reuters survey showed on Thursday.
articles.title: Ex-defence minister Ishiba tops corporate Japan's premier wish list, Reuters poll shows

articles.author: Filipp Lebedev, Felix Light, Jessica Donati
articles.description: Among the dozens of Wagner mercenaries presumed dead after a lethal battle with Tuareg rebels during a desert sandstorm in Mali in July were Russian war veterans who survived tours in Ukraine, Libya and Syria, according to interviews with relatives and a review of social media data.
articles.title: Exclusive: Wagner lost veteran fighters in Mali ambush, in setback to Russia's Africa campaign
